                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>\n                <date>Sept 15<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1858</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir</p>\n            <p>From every part of the <placeName>U States</placeName> Donations<lb/> are daily recd\n                by our Various Benevolent<lb/> Institutions to assist their\n                <sic>releiving</sic><lb/> the sick &amp; Indigent while religious<lb/> Institutions\n                are also in receipt of<lb/> Various Sums to defray the Expense<lb/> of Burying the\n                Dead These Donations<lb/> come from Christians to Christians<lb/> one House\n                    (<sic>Jewellers</sic>) or our City<lb/> I forget the name (a Handsome white<lb/>\n                marble Front Store on <placeName>Chestnut St</placeName>)<lb/> sent our Howard\n                Association $500.00<lb/> I need not tell you How exhausted<lb/> any Treasury becomes\n                when the<lb/> drain is constant for doctors<lb/> nurses medicines &amp;c. Our\n                President<lb/> of the Gent Hebr. Ben Association<lb/>\n                <persName>L B Cain Esq</persName> has worked hard &amp;<lb/> Business Health &amp;c\n                is neglected<lb/> by him in his constant Labour<lb/> of seeing to the sick. Our congregation<lb/>\n                <placeName>Rampart Sr.</placeName> has <sic>allready</sic> Buried<lb/> about 50 all\n                Charity &amp; of course</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pz5267n/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
