                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pz5267n/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>a very Heavy outlay for their exhausted<lb/> Treasury, our “Home” must take<lb/> in a\n                large number of orphans<lb/> left Destitute Oh its a sad scene<lb/> to witness &amp;\n                I will not call up<lb/> the better feelings of your nature by<lb/> recounting all\n                the misery<lb/> we witness here our Jewish<lb/> people of both sexes work<lb/> hard\n                &amp; faithful &amp; are many<lb/> of them completely worn out!<lb/> The Fever still\n                continues its<lb/> fatal work carrying off whole<lb/> &amp; frequently portions of a\n                family.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Its to be hoped our <sic>Bretheren</sic><lb/> of your own admission\n                Cities will<lb/> not wait a similar call to one<lb/> we made (&amp; I am happy to\n                acknow<lb/>ledge not in vain) once before<lb/> but some Influential good\n                    Philantro<lb/><sic>phists</sic> will be found to go to work &amp;<lb/> send some\n                relief ere its too late<lb/> Excuse this hasty scrawl yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">ever Truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Isaac Hart</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p><persName>Mr DeSilva</persName> paid me $25.00 for the Hebrew Prayer Books (11)</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pz5267n/canvas/p2"
                }
